MacroMolecule.Polymer.AtomIterator

public MacroMolecule.Polymer.AtomIterator(int fromResidue,
                                          int toResidue)
Creates an iterator that enumerates all atoms of the polymer between the specified range of residue numbers. Hydrogen atoms are not listed unless setIncludeHydrogens( true ) is called.

Parameters:
fromResidue - residue number of the first residue listed
toResidue - residue number of the last residue listed

current

public int current()
Gets the index of the current atom without moving to the next atoms. This method can be called as often as needed.
Note, that this index can be used in AtomPropertyInterfaces to access atomic properties.

getCount

public int getCount()
Gets the maximum number of atoms the iterator returns. Note: Hydrogen enumeration is taked into acount but residue number range is ignored (ie. a larger number than actual number atoms enumerated is returned). This is safe though not the desired way of operation. Will be fixed in futere releases.

Specified by:
getCount in interface MoleculeIterators.AtomIteratorInterface
Returns:
maximum number of atoms iterated
